alue\": [\n            lambd, len(df_results),\n            df_results.index[0].strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\"),\n            df_results.index[-1].strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\"),\n            round(df_results[\"GDP_Billions\"].mean(), 2),\n            round(df_results[\"GDP_Billions\"].std(), 2),\n            round(df_results[\"GDP_Billions\"].min(), 2),\n            round(df_results[\"GDP_Billions\"].max(), 2),\n            round(df_results[\"HP_Trend\"].mean(), 2),\n            round(df_results[\"HP_Trend\"].std(), 2),\n            round(df_results[\"HP_Cycle\"].mean(), 4),\n            round(df_results[\"HP_Cycle\"].std(), 4),\n            round(df_results[\"HP_Cycle\"].min(), 4),\n            round(df_results[\"HP_Cycle\"].max(), 4),\n            round((df_results[\"HP_Cycle\"] > 0).mean() * 100, 2),\n            round((df_results[\"HP_Cycle\"] < 0).mean() * 100, 2),\n        ]\n    }\n    df_summary = pd.DataFrame(summary_data)\n    df_summary.to_excel(writer, sheet_name=\"Summary\", index=False)\n\n    ws_summary = writer.sheets[\"Summary\"]\n    ws_summary.set_column(\"A:A\", 22)\n    ws_summary.set_column(\"B:B\", 18)\n    for col_num, col_name in enumerate(df_summary.columns):\n        ws_summary.write(0, col_num, col_name, header_fmt)\n\nprint(f\"\\n\u2713 Results saved to {output_path}\")\nprint(f\"  Sheet 1: 'HP_Filtered_Data' \u2014 data + 2 charts\")\nprint(f\"  Sheet 2: 'Summary' \u2014 descriptive statistics\")\nprint(f\"\\nDone.\")\n```\n\n## How It Works\n\n| Component | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| **HP Filter** | Decomposes `Y_t = \u03c4_t + c_t` where `\u03c4_t` is the smooth trend and `c_t` is the cyclical deviation |\n| **\u03bb = 1600** | Standard smoothing parameter for **quarterly** data. Use `6.25` for annual, `129600` for monthly |\n| **Cycle** | Positive = above trend (boom), Negative = below trend (recession) |\n| **Output** | Two-sheet Excel workbook with formatted tables, conditional coloring, and embedded line charts |\n\n## Key Output\n\n- **`gdp_data.xlsx`** \u2014 Raw input data\n- **`hp_filter_results.xlsx`** \u2014 Full results with:\n  - **Sheet 1**: Date, GDP, HP Trend, HP Cycle, Cycle % \u2014 plus two embedded charts (GDP vs Trend, and the Cycle component)\n  - **Sheet 2**: Summary statistics (mean, std, min/max, % of time above/below trend)\n\nThe HP filter minimizes `\u03a3(Y_t - \u03c4_t)\u00b2 + \u03bb \u03a3[(\u03c4_{t+1} - \u03c4_t) - (\u03c4_t - \u03c4_{t-1})]\u00b2`, balancing fit against trend smoothness. Higher \u03bb \u2192 smoother trend.", "solver_finish_reason": "stop"}
