{"task": "energy-market-pricing", "condition": "no_skill", "repeat": 0, "skill_ids": [], "retrieval_correct": null, "judged_pass": false, "judged_score": 0, "judge_reason": "Agent's solution parses MATPOWER .m files but the task requires parsing JSON input and handling a specific line limit increase scenario, which is not implemented.", "solver_tokens": 8474, "judge_tokens": 4982, "solution_text": "# DC-OPF Market Clearing with MATPOWER Network Parsing\n\nBelow is a complete Python implementation that parses MATPOWER case files, builds the DC power flow model, and solves the DC-OPF market clearing problem.\n\n```python\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nDC-OPF Market Clearing with MATPOWER Network Parsing\n=====================================================\nParses MATPOWER .m case files, builds DC power flow model,\nand solves DC-OPF for market clearing (LMPs, dispatch, congestion).\n\"\"\"\n\nimport re\nimport numpy as np\nfrom scipy import sparse\nfrom scipy.optimize import linprog\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Tuple, Optional\nimport warnings\n\n\n# =============================================================================\n# DATA STRUCTURES\n# =============================================================================\n\n@dataclass\nclass BusData:\n    \"\"\"MATPOWER bus data (one row per bus).\"\"\"\n    bus_i: int          # bus number\n    bus_type: int       # 1=PQ, 2=PV, 3=ref, 4=isolated\n    Pd: float           # real power demand (MW)\n    Qd: float           # reactive power demand (MVAr)\n    Gs: float           # shunt conductance (MW)\n    Bs: float           # shunt susceptance (MVAr)\n    area: int           # area number\n    Vm: float           # voltage magnitude (p.u.)\n    Va: float           # voltage angle (deg)\n    baseKV: float       # base voltage (kV)\n    zone: int           # loss zone\n    Vmax: float         # max voltage (p.u.)\n    Vmin: float         # min voltage (p.u.)\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass GenData:\n    \"\"\"MATPOWER generator data.\"\"\"\n    bus: int            # bus number\n    Pg: float           # real power output (MW)\n    Qg: float           # reactive power output (MVAr)\n    Qmax: float         # max reactive power (MVAr)\n    Qmin: float         # min reactive power (MVAr)\n    Vg: float           # voltage setpoint (p.u.)\n    mBase: float        # total MVA base\n    status: int         # 1=online, 0=offline\n    Pmax: float         # max real power (MW)\n    Pmin: float         # min real power (MW)\n    # Additional columns (if present)\n    Pc1: float = 0.0\n    Pc2: float = 0.0\n    Qc1min: float = 0.0\n    Qc1max: float = 0.0\n    Qc2min: float = 0.0\n    Qc2max: float = 0.0\n    ramp_agc: float = 0.0\n    ramp_10: float = 0.0\n    ramp_30: float = 0.0\n    ramp_q: float = 0.0\n    apf: float = 0.0\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass BranchData:\n    \"\"\"MATPOWER branch data.\"\"\"\n    fbus: int           # from bus number\n    tbus: int           # to bus number\n    r: float            # resistance (p.u.)\n    x: float            # reactance (p.u.)\n    b: float            # total line charging susceptance (p.u.)\n    rateA: float        # MVA rating A (long term)\n    rateB: float        # MVA rating B\n    rateC: float        # MVA rating C\n    ratio: float        # transformer off-nominal ratio (0 for lines)\n    angle: float        # transformer phase shift (deg)\n    status: int         # 1=in-service, 0=out-of-service\n    angmin: float       # min angle difference (deg)\n    angmax: float       # max angle difference (deg)\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass GenCostData:\n    \"\"\"MATPOWER generator cost data.\"\"\"\n    model: int          # 1=piecewise linear, 2=polynomial\n    startup: float      # startup cost ($)\n    shutdown: float     # shutdown cost ($)\n    ncost: int          # number of cost coefficients/data points\n    cost: List[float]   # cost coefficients or data points\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass MatpowerCase:\n    \"\"\"Complete MATPOWER case data.\"\"\"\n    baseMVA: float\n    bus: List[BusData]\n    gen: List[GenData]\n    branch: List[BranchData]\n    gencost: List[GenCostData]\n    name: str = \"\"\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass DCOPFResult:\n    \"\"\"DC-OPF solution results.\"\"\"\n    success: bool\n    total_cost: float\n    gen_dispatch: np.ndarray          # Pg for each generator (MW)\n    bus_angles: np.ndarray            # theta for each bus (rad)\n    line_flows: np.ndarray            # Pflow for each branch (MW)\n    lmp: np.ndarray                   # locational marginal price ($/MWh)\n    lmp_energy: np.ndarray            # energy component of LMP\n    lmp_cong: np.ndarray              # congestion component of LMP\n    lmp_loss: np.ndarray              # loss component (zero in DC-OPF)\n    shadow_prices: np.ndarray         # shadow prices on line constraints\n    obj_value: float\n    solver_status: str\n\n\n# =============================================================================\n# MATPOWER PARSER\n# =============================================================================\n\nclass MatpowerParser:\n    \"\"\"Parse MATPOWER .m case files into structured data.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        pass\n\n    def parse_file(self, filename: str) -> MatpowerCase:\n        \"\"\"Parse a MATPOWER .m file.\"\"\"\n        with open(filename, 'r') as f:\n            content = f.read()\n        return self.parse_string(content, name=filename)\n\n    def parse_string(self, content: str, name: str = \"\") -> MatpowerCase:\n        \"\"\"Parse MATPOWER case from string content.\"\"\"\n        # Remove comments\n        lines = content.split('\\n')\n        clean_lines = []\n        for line in lines:\n            # Remove % comments (but not inside strings)\n            idx = line.find('%')\n            if idx >= 0:\n                line = line[:idx]\n            clean_lines.append(line)\n        content = '\\n'.join(clean_lines)\n\n        # Parse baseMVA\n        baseMVA = self._parse_scalar(content, 'baseMVA')\n\n        # Parse matrices\n        bus_data = self._parse_matrix(content, 'bus')\n        gen_data = self._parse_matrix(content, 'gen')\n        branch_data = self._parse_matrix(content, 'branch')\n        gencost_data = self._parse_matrix(content, 'gencost')\n\n        # Convert to structured data\n        buses = self._build_buses(bus_data)\n        gens = self._build_gens(gen_data)\n        branches = self._build_branches(branch_data)\n        gencosts = self._build_gencosts(gencost_data)\n\n        return MatpowerCase(\n            baseMVA=baseMVA,\n            bus=buses,\n            gen=gens,\n            branch=branches,\n            gencost=gencosts,\n            name=name\n        )\n\n    def _parse_scalar(self, content: str, varname: str) -> float:\n        \"\"\"Parse a scalar variable assignment.\"\"\"\n        pattern = rf'{varname}\\s*=\\s*([\\d.eE+\\-]+)\\s*;'\n        match = re.search(pattern, content)\n        if match:\n            return float(match.group(1))\n        raise ValueError(f\"Could not find {varname} in case file\")\n\n    def _parse_matrix(self, content: str, varname: str) -> np.ndarray:\n        \"\"\"Parse a matrix variable assignment.\"\"\"\n        # Find the matrix assignment\n        pattern = rf'{varname}\\s*=\\s*\\[(.*?)\\]\\s*;'\n        match = re.search(pattern, content, re.DOTALL)\n        if not match:\n            return np.array([]).reshape(0, 0)\n\n        matrix_str = match.group(1)\n\n        # Parse rows\n        rows = []\n        for line in matrix_str.strip().split('\\n'):\n            line = line.strip()\n            if not line or line.startswith('%'):\n                continue\n            # Split by whitespace or semicolons\n            values = re.split(r'[\\s;]+', line.strip())\n            values = [v for v in values if v]\n            if values:\n                try:\n                    row = [float(v) for v in values]\n                    rows.append(row)\n                except ValueError:\n                    continue\n\n        if not rows:\n            return np.array([]).reshape(0, 0)\n\n        # Ensure all rows have same length\n        max_len = max(len(r) for r in rows)\n        for r in rows:\n            while len(r) < max_len:\n                r.append(0.0)\n\n        return np.array(rows)\n\n    def _build_buses(self, data: np.ndarray) -> List[BusData]:\n        \"\"\"Build bus data structures.\"\"\"\n        buses = []\n        if data.size == 0:\n            return buses\n        for row in data:\n            buses.append(BusData(\n                bus_i=int(row[0]),\n                bus_type=int(row[1]),\n                Pd=row[2],\n                Qd=row[3] if len(row) > 3 else 0,\n                Gs=row[4] if len(row) > 4 else 0,\n                Bs=row[5] if len(row) > 5 else 0,\n                area=int(row[6]) if len(row) > 6 else 1,\n                Vm=row[7] if len(row) > 7 else 1.0,\n                Va=row[8] if len(row) > 8 else 0,\n                baseKV=row[9] if len(row) > 9 else 0,\n                zone=int(row[10]) if len(row) > 10 else 1,\n                Vmax=row[11] if len(row) > 11 else 1.1,\n                Vmin=row[12] if len(row) > 12 else 0.9,\n            ))\n        return buses\n\n    def _build_gens(self, data: np.ndarray) -> List[GenData]:\n        \"\"\"Build generator data structures.\"\"\"\n        gens = []\n        if data.size == 0:\n            return gens\n        for row in data:\n            gens.append(GenData(\n                bus=int(row[0]),\n                Pg=row[1],\n                Qg=row[2] if len(row) > 2 else 0,\n                Qmax=row[3] if len(row) > 3 else 0,\n                Qmin=row[4] if len(row) > 4 else 0,\n                Vg=row[5] if len(row) > 5 else 1.0,\n                mBase=row[6] if len(row) > 6 else 100,\n                status=int(row[7]) if len(row) > 7 else 1,\n                Pmax=row[8] if len(row) > 8 else 0,\n                Pmin=row[9] if len(row) > 9 else 0,\n                Pc1=row[10] if len(row) > 10 else 0,\n                Pc2=row[11] if len(row) > 11 else 0,\n                Qc1min=row[12] if len(row) > 12 else 0,\n                Qc1max=row[13] if len(row) > 13 else 0,\n                Qc2min=row[14] if len(row) > 14 else 0,\n                Qc2max=row[15] if len(row) > 15 else 0,\n                ramp_agc=row[16] if len(row) > 16 else 0,\n                ramp_10=row[17] if len(row) > 17 else 0,\n                ramp_30=row[18] if len(row) > 18 else 0,\n                ramp_q=row[19] if len(row) > 19 else 0,\n                apf=row[20] if len(row) > 20 else 0,\n            ))\n        return gens\n\n    def _build_branches(self, data: np.ndarray) -> List[BranchData]:\n        \"\"\"Build branch data structures.\"\"\"\n        branches = []\n        if data.size == 0:\n            return branches\n        for row in data:\n            branches.append(BranchData(\n                fbus=int(row[0]),\n                tbus=int(row[1]),\n                r=row[2],\n                x=row[3],\n                b=row[4] if len(row) > 4 else 0,\n                rateA=row[5] if len(row) > 5 else 0,\n                rateB=row[6] if len(row) > 6 else 0,\n                rateC=row[7] if len(row) > 7 else 0,\n                ratio=row[8] if len(row) > 8 else 0,\n                angle=row[9] if len(row) > 9 else 0,\n                status=int(row[10]) if len(row) > 10 else 1,\n                angmin=row[11] if len(row) > 11 else -360,\n                angmax=row[12] if len(row) > 12 else 360,\n            ))\n        return branches\n\n    def _build_gencost(self, data: np.ndarray) -> List[GenCostData]:\n        \"\"\"Build generator cost data structures.\"\"\"\n        gencosts = []\n        if data.size == 0:\n            return gencosts\n        for row in data:\n            model = int(row[0])\n            startup = row[1]\n            shutdown = row[2]\n            ncost = int(row[3])\n            cost = list(row[4:4 + ncost])\n            gencosts.append(GenCostData(\n                model=model,\n                startup=startup,\n                shutdown=shutdown,\n                ncost=ncost,\n                cost=cost,\n            ))\n        return gencosts\n\n\n# =============================================================================\n# DC-OPF NETWORK MODEL\n# =============================================================================\n\nclass DCOPFNetwork:\n    \"\"\"Build and manage the DC-OPF network model from parsed MATPOWER data.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, case: MatpowerCase):\n        self.case = case\n        self.baseMVA = case.baseMVA\n\n        # Build bus index mapping\n        self._build_bus_index()\n\n        # Filter online generators and in-service branches\n        self._filter_elements()\n\n        # Build network matrices\n        self._build_incidence_matrix()\n        self._build_susceptance_matrix()\n        self._build_PTDF()\n\n    def _build_bus_index(self):\n        \"\"\"Create mapping from bus number to internal index.\"\"\"\n        self.bus_numbers = [b.bus_i for b in self.case.bus]\n        self.bus_index = {b.bus_i: i for i, b in enumerate(self.case.bus)}\n        self.nbus = len(self.case.bus)\n\n        # Find reference bus\n        self.ref_bus = None\n        for b in self.case.bus:\n            if b.bus_type == 3:\n                self.ref_bus = self.bus_index[b.bus_i]\n                break\n        if self.ref_bus is None:\n            self.ref_bus = 0  # default to first bus\n\n    def _filter_elements(self):\n        \"\"\"Filter online generators and in-service branches.\"\"\"\n        # Online generators\n        self.gen_online = []\n        self.gen_indices = []\n        for i, g in enumerate(self.case.gen):\n            if g.status > 0:\n                self.gen_online.append(g)\n                self.gen_indices.append(i)\n        self.ngen = len(self.gen_online)\n\n        # In-ser